    {
      "id": "68",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Remus",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/05/19/237301566/31941f53b43891e840dd1997518ccef4_1325281874186918335.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In times when the people of the High Sea lived in ignorance, and the tribes were unenlightened, the Philharmonic God, Remus, ruled in the Sumeru Desert. He was once a singer of the oases, but his ancient home had been lost beneath the light of King Deshret. Unwilling to serve his throne, Remus chose the path of wandering. The Philharmonic God had picked the High Sea for his grave, but when wandering in that land he saw the ruins of a city. The ruins were older than the land itself. The city was never mentioned in any chronicles and existed below the lightless abyssal depths. Right there, in the heart of the ruined temple, beneath the silver-white cedar, happened the first meeting of future glorified king Remus and a Golden Bee, Sybilla, who could see the future. Sybilla predicted that Remus would rule cities and subjects once more. The nation he built would flourish and prosper, and he would one day rule the entire High Sea. Even though Remus would bring civilization and justice to the people, in the end, that very justice would be their downfall.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"When the fated time of judgment comes, the merciless waves will devour fleeting glory and happiness.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The Philharmonic God knew that there was no point in resisting fate, and so he agreed to set out on that journey. As he made his choice, the waterless hollow crumbled with a crash, the silver tree turning into a golden ship \"Fortuna.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/05/19/237301566/fa8329bb7cc10e0fd51ddf52f0c31797_2305432044969375017.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Aboard the \"Fortuna,\" Remus and Sybilla descended upon Meropis. Before Remus's arrival, the land was inhabited by ancient people. They lived in peace and harmony, and even envoys of Celestia walked the earth. After countless generations, the people decided that they wanted to be free from the chains of fate. Enraged by that, the Heavens destroyed the ancient people. Only when Remus entered those lands again did prosperity and order reappear there. He taught people how to farm and raise crops in the land and built temples and cities with huge stones to house the people. Most importantly, it was he who spread the beauty of music and art, which differentiated humans from other living things, causing them to see themselves as masters of all things. The Philharmonic God built a great tower in Meropis, gathering the scattered people to build a new nation. The horns of abundance blessed the land with fertility, and an endless maritime parade connected the islands as one.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4813,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/04/30/237301566/4f78eb7e03b130ca2efba77b4d2692bb_1435824995413402244.png",
                      "menu_id": 22,
                      "name": "Ремурия",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4911,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/03/237301566/513d51e0ebfd54f5da34a9f85dfaf61f_2834910047270303942.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Аль-Ахмар",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 5578,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/04/19/237301566/7557f4558ab243d82e8b6b9994fc97ee_8729707325921240825.png",
                      "menu_id": 5,
                      "name": "Фрагмент гармонической фантазии",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4325,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/09/18/94376896/d0e75f9b88a286749b4c7dff0871e129_3058308201433029321.png",
                      "menu_id": 12,
                      "name": "The History of the Decline and Fall of Remuria",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Prophecy",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Even as the nation continued to grow and prosper, the original prophecy was never forgotten, and the king's doubts remained.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Just as you foretold, I have become a glorious king, bringing cultured civilization to the people.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "I have bestowed peace unto the ocean, and govern the land with justice, spreading order and progress to every corner of the earth.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "Yet the more prosperous my new, glorious realm grew, the more mournful and perplexed I became.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "The prophesied glory will continue for a century, and then? The seeds of destruction are taking root.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Change is the nature of things, such is the law of Fortuna. Even acknowledging the foolishness about eternity and immortality, Remus couldn't reconcile with the bleak future. He turned to the seer but she could not help: she was able to see the future, but she lacked the ancient, sacred wisdom to explore the cause of the destruction.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"But I know, in the deepest depths of the lightless sea, in the realm where the Primordial Waters yet surge, the Mistress of Many Waters lies imprisoned.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "As the prophecy foretells that the endless waves will swallow your nation, perhaps she may have answers...\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Following Sybilla's advice, Remus, along with the Golden Fleet, sailed to find the sea where the Mistress of Many Waters, Egeria, was imprisoned. It was the kingdom where the Dragonborn dwelled, called the Fontemer. Led by the Dragon Prince, Scylla, Vishaps guarded the prison of Egeria. Both sides began to fight, and the resulting battle boiled the seas for thirty days and thirty nights. It was only when exhaustion brought respite that the God King used music to voice his purpose. Remus's will to resist fate, rite by the Heavenly Principles, amused the Dragon Prince. Even though Remus's dream seemed ridiculous to him, Scylla agreed to take Remus to the Mistress of Many Waters.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Merciful Egeria couldn't give Remus the answer he was looking for. In the end, the king, who still harbored ambition and hope, decided to take a cup of the",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "given by the Mistress of Many Waters before leaving. He promised her to use the pure water she granted to create a world of endless prosperity, one without conflict. When the fleet was returning back home, Scylla also left the Fontemer. Although all gods were usurpers to Vishaps, Scylla and Remus became friends.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4813,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/04/30/237301566/4f78eb7e03b130ca2efba77b4d2692bb_1435824995413402244.png",
                      "menu_id": 22,
                      "name": "Ремурия",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
